# [GREEN](../wg/green.html)

## Summary

The GREEN working group met at IETF 126 to discuss the progress of its core deliverables, evaluate newly adopted works, and consider related drafts for potential adoption or cross-working-group collaboration. The session was chaired by Rob Wilton and Diego Lopez. Excellent progress has been made since IETF 125, with several core documents now adopted. The group discussed alignments across terminology, use cases, and the framework, finalized key updates on the base device YANG model, and initiated structural scoping for a controller-level YANG model. Additionally, experimental results from the recent Hackathon were shared, and several new proposals in areas such as telemetry provenance, IPFIX energy consumption, and multicast eco-modes were discussed.

